# CONTRACT (T8 harness, crates/core/tests/ui.rs): each non-comment, non-blank
# line below is a substring that MUST appear somewhere in the sample's real
# compiler diagnostic. The harness asserts ONLY that the sample FAILS to compile
# and that every substring appears — never exact prose, wording, note count, or
# span layout — so ordinary compiler-message churn does not break the suite
# (C3; C17; C28; pinned to the workspace toolchain per rust-toolchain.toml).
#
# A teardown never has a data dependency, enforced at COMPILE time: the
# `register_teardown` seam takes a consume-nothing task (`Task<Input = ()>`)
# because a teardown fires on the non-default `all-terminal` rule, which C3's
# builder typestate makes inexpressible on a data-consuming node. Passing a task
# whose `Input` is not `()` fails the trait bound. The stable, toolchain-pinned
# substrings are the method name `register_teardown` and the unsatisfied
# associated-type constraint on the input.
